==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eastern
<hw>East"ern</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>e⟦aacute⟧stern</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Situated or dwelling
in the east; oriental; <as>as, an <ex>eastern</ex> gate;
<ex>Eastern</ex> countries.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Eastern</qex> churches first did Christ embrace.</q>
<rj><qau>Stirling.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Going toward the east, or in the direction of east;
<as>as, an <ex>eastern</ex> voyage</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eastern Church</ent>⟦br⟧
